                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/120: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-16T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 16, 1935—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 16—6:09 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Consulate’s 19, January 15, 4 p.m. Late last evening Abyssinian delegate
                    handed to the Secretary General an appeal to the Council<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d468fn5">See League of Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official
                            Journal</hi>, February 1935, pp. 252–258.</note> under article XI,
                    paragraph 2, of the Covenant.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
